						<summary>

						<p>Pāṇḍya, Māṟavarman Sundarapāṇḍya I, 15th year = A.D. 1231.</p>						

						<p>Āḍavallānambi <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Magadarāyaṉ who had worked as the agent of Chērapāṇḍiyadēvar the administrator of the locality and succeeded him as the nāḍu settlement officer <hi rend="italic">(nāḍu kēṭṭaruḷi)</hi> made some new arrangement for offerings to the goddess in the Tiruvaraṅguḷam-uḍaiya-nāyaṉar temple.</p>						

